<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A woman has died in a horror crash between a car and truck in Sydney's south.</p>

<p>Emergency services were called to the intersection of Coward and Bourke streets in Mascot following the collision around 12.30pm on Wednesday.</p>

<p>A woman was trapped inside the car for a short time before being released but died at the scene.</p>

<p>The truck driver suffered minor injuries and was taken to Prince of Wales Hospital for mandatory testing.</p>

<p>Police are investigating the circumstances surrounding the crash and remain at the scene.</p>

<p>Motorists are urged to avoid the area as several roads in the area are closed.</p>

<p>A report will be prepared for the Coroner.</p>
